name: Donna M. PAGLIARINI v. DOYLE'S SERVICE, INC. v. Charles H. O'CONNELL, Finance Director of the City of East Providence

parties: Donna M. PAGLIARINI v. DOYLE’S SERVICE, INC. v. Charles H. O’CONNELL, Finance Director of the City of East Providence.

opinions.text:
ORDER
The motion of defendant Doyle’s Service, Inc. to affirm the judgment of the Superior Court pursuant to Rule 16(g) is denied.
WEISBERGER, J., did not participate.

attorneys: Aram K. Berberian, Warwick, for plaintiff.
Gilbert T. Rocha, Joseph B. Carty, Jr., Providence, for Doyle’s Service, Inc., Nathaniel J. Rendine, Asst. Sol., East Providence, for defendants.
casebody.head_matter:
Donna M. PAGLIARINI v. DOYLE’S SERVICE, INC. v. Charles H. O’CONNELL, Finance Director of the City of East Providence.
No. 81-289-A.
Supreme Court of Rhode Island.
July 23, 1981.
Aram K. Berberian, Warwick, for plaintiff.
Gilbert T. Rocha, Joseph B. Carty, Jr., Providence, for Doyle’s Service, Inc., Nathaniel J. Rendine, Asst. Sol., East Providence, for defendants.
